 To simplify the given expression, we first factor out the square roots and simplify the fractions. 

\begin{align*} \frac{\sqrt{507}}{\sqrt{48}} - \frac{\sqrt{175}}{\sqrt{112}} &= \frac{\sqrt{13\times 39}}{\sqrt{16\times3}} - \frac{\sqrt{25\times7}}{\sqrt{16\times7}}\\ &= \frac{\sqrt{13}\times\sqrt{39}}{4\sqrt{3}} - \frac{5}{4}\\ &= \frac{\sqrt{13}\times\sqrt{13\times3}}{4\sqrt{3}} - \frac{5}{4}\\ &= \frac{\sqrt{13}\times\sqrt{13}\times\sqrt{3}}{4\sqrt{3}} - \frac{5}{4}\\ &= \frac{13}{4} - \frac{5}{4}\\ &= \boxed{\frac{8}{4}} \end{align*}

Answer: $\frac{8}{4}$

